            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "In paq-nvim, the lockfile is just used to check if an installed package has version/URL mismatch with what users specify in their config. So their lockfile is just a JSON-ized version of their `Packages` object\n```json5\n{\n    \"package-1\": {\n       \"name\": \"package-1\",\n       \"url\": \"https://.../package-1.git\"\n       \"hash\": \"...\"\n       // Other field of Package that can be serialized\n   },\n    \"pack2\": {\n        \"name\": \"pack2\",\n        \"url\":  \"\"\n        \"hash\": \"...\"\n        // etc\n    }\n}\n```\nAlso since pkg.json's lockfile is called `pkg.lock.json` instead of `pkg-lock.json`, does that mean it doesn't have to be a subset of npm's `package-lock.json`?",
